{{nihongo|'''Keiko Chiba'''|<U+5343><U+8449> <U+666F><U+5B50>|extra=born May 11, 1948}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[politician]] of the [[Democratic Party of Japan]], a member of the [[House of Councillors]] in the [[Diet of Japan|Diet]] (national legislature). A native of [[Yokohama, Kanagawa]] and graduate of [[Chuo University]], she was elected to the House of Councillors for the first time in 1986. She became the [[Minister of Justice (Japan)]] in [[Yukio Hatoyama]]'s cabinet on September 16, 2009. 

She is a prominent member of anti-death penalty organization in Japan, and many legal analysts{{Who|date=September 2009}} criticize Chiba's appointment. She also expresses support for illegal immigrants in Japan, and she even said before that all illegal immigrants in Japan should be allowed to stay in Japan without any legal documentation.{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}

